## **ğŸ”§ Setup & Installation**

### **1ï¸âƒ£ Prerequisites**

Ensure you have the following installed:

- [Golang](https://go.dev/dl/) (v1.21+)
- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/get-started)
- [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)
- [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community) (if running locally without Docker)

### **2ï¸âƒ£ Clone the Repository**

```sh
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/link-in-bio-api.git
cd link-in-bio-api
```

### **3ï¸âƒ£ Set Up Environment Variables**

Create a `.env` file in the root directory:

```env
MONGO_URI=mongodb://mongodb:27017
PORT=8080
WORKER_COUNT=10
```



---

## **ğŸ³ Running with Docker**

### **1ï¸âƒ£ Build and Start Containers**

```sh
docker-compose up --build
```

This will:

- Build the **Go app**
- Start **MongoDB**
- Expose the API on **port 8080**

### **2ï¸âƒ£ Verify Running Containers**

```sh
docker ps
```

You should see **MongoDB** and **Go API** running.

### **3ï¸âƒ£ Stop Containers**

```sh
docker-compose down
```

---

## **âš¡ Running Locally (Without Docker)**

### **1ï¸âƒ£ Start MongoDB Locally**

Ensure MongoDB is running on `localhost:27017`:

```sh
mongod --dbpath=/path/to/your/data
```

### **2ï¸âƒ£ Install Dependencies**

```sh
go mod tidy
```

### **3ï¸âƒ£ Run the Application**

```sh
go run main.go
```

The API should now be running on **[http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)** ğŸš€

---

## **ğŸ›  API Endpoints**

### **ğŸ”¹ Create a New Link**

```http
POST /api/v1/links
```

#### **Request Body**

```json
{
  "id": "3",
  "title": "Test Link",
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "createdAt": "2023-10-01T00:00:00Z",
  "expiresAt": "2023-10-08T00:00:00Z",
  "clicks": 0
}
```

#### **Response**

```json
{
   "ID": "4",
    "Title": "Test Link",
    "URL": "https://example.com",
    "CreatedAt": "2023-10-01T00:00:00Z",
    "ExpiresAt": "2023-10-08T00:00:00Z",
    "Clicks": 0
}
```

### **ğŸ”¹ Get a Link**

```http
GET /api/v1/links/{id}
```

### **ğŸ”¹ Track Clicks**

```http
GET /api/v1/visit/{id}
```

